CJD - GERMANY
==============
Date: Wed, 19 Jun 1996 07:03:02 -0700
From: Kari Koester-Loesche <loesche@AXOS.COM>
Subject: Re: Reports of V-CJD in Germany?

Jenny Cann wrote:
>
> I'm wondering if anyone can help me on this one:
>
> Apparantly there have been reports appearing "somewhere on the Internet"
> of cases of V-CJD appearing in Germany. I have been told that Der
> Speigel of 1/4/96 refers to this. Unfortunately I dont have access to
> this publication and I wondered if anyone out there does and can give me
> some further details (the above onformation came to me by word of mouth
> and therefore may not be reliable, hence the quotes)
>
> Thanks for your help.
> --
> Jenny Cann (jenny@hefinfo.demon.co.uk)


I've found the article in "Der Spiegel". It reports that since the middle of
1993 a total of 154 brains were examined: plaques as those of the 10 british
V-CJD were not found. Explicitly, it was referred to:

- a 36 year old woman working as a catering assistant and being frequently in
contact with calv brain.

- an owner of a pet shop having frequently eaten soup on basis of marrowbone

- a butcher

- between Oct 1993 and Oct 1994 6 farmers with CJD

The "lifelong vegetarian from Germany" and the one who "had lived in
Australia for the last 12 years" in Oz's message reading..., dated Tue, 18 Jun 96 20:59:18> weren't mentioned in this article.

Regards,

Kari Koester-Loesche

