The Australian was apparently considered a UK case for some reason.

If I understand you correctly then NO cases with the flower-like plaques
have been reported in Germany as far as the Der Spiegel article in May
96 is concerned. So I can presume that none are implicated with V-CJD
and that these are normal sporadic cases.

--
O.F.A. Hotz de Baar. UK

